  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building resileince of drought affected communities in N.Horr</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">-Increased capacity of communities to progressively use PRA processes to generate and link CAPs to County budget and planning processes
-Improved DRR capacity and community asset base through Self-Help model
- support emergency preparedness through community led approaches to disaster management and response
- community granting to support implementation of action plans 
- increased access to clean and safe water for human and livestock use
- accountability to affected communities</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">-increased drought affected communities&apos; absorptive,adaptive, anticipatory capacity in managing disasaters
- increased community resilience to drought and other hazards trough strengthening social protection under SHGs
- strengthened community preparedness and response capacity through supporting CAPs implementation and community led response initiatives 
-increased accountability and transparency in use of community water facility</narrative>
  </description>
